caption: Great low-frills place in Park Slope for a chill drink! Good outdoor patio for those sunny covid days. Unlike other establishments, they won't force you to order an entree and will provide a snack for you if you get a drink (thanks for the sandwich!!).
Great craft variety.
This place is a staple of the area.  Check out the back garden area for fresh air and a cold one. The only BS you need is Beers and Sunshine.

Me and my girlfriend had our 1st date here, probably not the best place to go for a first date because we got so drunk!! lol the drinks were bomb and the bartenders were very friendly! this particular day they were charging a entry fee to get in, and the host at the door let me in free because she said I was "beautiful" :) she made my day!! recommend this place during football season!!!
7 dollar pints
Thin selection post covid. Hopefully the full menu appears later. Was a place of many l choices and general quality in the past. May those days return.

Authentic Gothic dive bar with great neighborhood vibe! Great craft beer selection, and Freshest beer in Park Slope, always friendly crowd of patrons, and super nice staff. Their location can't be beat in the heart of Park Slope, across the street from historical Washington Park. Reasonably priced beer, and drinks.  Highly recommend this place to all!
One of my locals...great beer selection, friendly bartenders, cozy inside and sun-drenched tables outside.
Been coming here for 20 years. Always a good time and great beer selection.
Nice environment good selection of beers! Good place to hang out!
Great beer bar!!
Best beer bar in the neighborhood. By a lot. Dark bar, but nice outdoor patio.
Goog place
A must see bar.
Love it

Great bar. Theres a lot to it. Really friendly crowd and staff. They have a side patio with lots of seating. They have a bunch of board games and cards free to play. They have a ton of beer and liquor. They have big buck hunter and pacman. They have darts and plenty of seating. Perfect!
Loved it! Cozy atmosphere and they had board games!
Very chill and affordable neighborhood vibe...no attitude
Nice place to chill after work and flirt with old men and recieve love and appreciation and give plenty of tip$
Great beer selection, bartender professional level dry humor.
Great craft beer bar. Has stood the test of time.
Classic park slope bar.
A great bar.  Not overly crowded.  Bar tender was friendly and quick to help us. Very nice outside seating.
Good food
Excellent selection of liquors and cocktails
Their patio is a wonderful place to spend the afternoon
Great staff. Great beer.
Beautiful patio!
Great service. Amazing beer selections.
A wonderful bar.  Bit of everything and supremely comfy.  Beer selection is boss and the staff is fabulous
Good old-fashioned Brooklyn dive
Wonderful bar

Great atmosphere for a pub experience. A dog friendly patio to boot.
Gated :)
A fantastic brew selection. Outstanding beer buyers present a fantastic selection as evidinced by my great time every visit over a 10+ year span.
I love this place, reasonable prices for beers and great knowledgeable staff.
Love  everything about it!
Best place for an afternoon drink! Especially when warm enough for the patio.
Great neighborhood bar
Cozy, divey.
Fun place for drinks, friends and games.
Friendly, non-trendy, old school local pub.
That bartender, I think her name's Rebekah, is ON POINT!
Fair prices, nice atmosphere
Relaxed unpretentious bar, good prices
Chilled out place. Love the outdoor space, weather permitting.
Great d4aft selection. Bring in  some pizza from the pizza place  a block away and you are set for a good night.
The gate is a great chill spot. outdoor area and allows dogs! also a great beer selection at a decent price. Bring your own food.

Really enjoyed my visit here.  Was hopping at a time when many other bars in the area were dead.  Cute dogs sleeping on the floor, a small reunion of friends from a local high school and a fantastic selection of craft beers equaled a very good time.  Also, the bathrooms are in the basement.  Not up those couple stairs halfway into the bar.  Don't bother going up there.  The bathrooms aren't there.

I've been going here for years and I keep going back and forth over whether it not I like the place. I love it when it's not that busy. They have a large outside area, so when the weather is nice they are flooded with people and dogs. The staff is always friendly and the service good. Lately they have started carrying cider which is great since I don't like beer. Be aware that even though they allow parents to bring children, they do NOT allow strollers inside the bar or in the outside seating area. If you are going to bring your kids leave the stroller at home.
Miserable bartender, bad vibe couldn't even stay long enough to finish our drinks, that's how bad the energy was in the place.
Miserable excuse of a bar .. unhappy bartender , poor service . Yuppie transplant sht hole
Great bar,  and they let you bring your own food. As someone that only eats kosher, it's a major plus!!!

A good beer selection with reasonable prices, and a chill outdoor space.  We came in after kitchen was closed so I can't speak for the food, but we got a few pizza slices from a nearby spot to take back to the outdoor garden area.  Also has a few board game options.
Best place to grab a beer in Brooklyn. It's pretty much just that though. Lots of taps. You will find a satisfying brew here.
Generally laid back vibe and good draft list. Chill spot. Unpretentious.
Really nice outside if you can get a table. Also have a great assortment of beers
Great place great service

I didn't have the opportunity to cross the gate. I arrived with my wife and little baby, a couple of friends and their baby. As we were with strollers, the bartender immediately told us to leave the strollers out. It was a terrible experience and I just can guess they are not comfortable with families going there as it's better for them to only receive adults in their restaurant.
Great outdoor seating area. Great selection! Also nice music inside. Wish they allowed dogs again.
Great place, nice environment and great food!
It's a pleasant atmosphere with an outside patio, music and Cocktails
Bar on 5th Avenue with low key vibe. Nice selection of draft beers. Has plenty of seating both inside and put. Has a slight dive bar feel but overall a warm place.
Great dive bar where you can have a conversation and hear each other without yelling. Drinks are reasonably priced.

Low key and grown up bar with great craft beer (and the usual other libations) classic rock playlist and a pro-dog policy.   You are welcome to bring outside food.  When its nice, the outside space is spacious and comfortable.
I'd give it 5 stars but I don't want too many outsiders going there. Neighborhood institution.
Good service, nice selection
Nice ambiance and enjoyed the Guinness draft
Good beer and enough room to be comfortable on a Saturday afternoon.
Nice place to chill during, spring , summer, fall.
OG beer bar in Park Slope. Big fixture in the community. Chill vibe. Always has a cool gem or 2. Dart board. Juke box. Outdoor patio.
Great local bar. No food, but lots of places nearby to grab something to go and get a beer at the bar. Good neighborhood hang
Good space with a bad bartender sadly

Cozy bar with great outdoor space (smoking allowed). Knowledgeable staff ready to help choose a great beer or cocktail
A great place to grab a brew with a awesome selection.

Great outdoor seating and good beer.
Great craft beer select and nice to hang outside.
Great dive bar that's not TOO divey.  Beer selection is crafty and delicious.  The outdoor patio is nice, plants are a cool touch
Relatively kid-free for the neighborhood.
Great local bar with awesome selections of beer and liquor. Friendly staff who know their trade. Good for a chilled evening that's laid back.
Underwhelming tap beer selection.
Classic Park Slope watering hole
Great atmosphere and great beer.  The garden area is spacious agree comfortable.
Decent local spot with a patio.

This was where we had informal staff meetings when the new boss started at our company and wanted us to like her.  nice regular bar with a patio right on the street so you can pretend you are an animal in a zoo.  One suggestion I would have is to install a peanut machine on the outside of the patio so pedestrians can pay a quarter for a handful of peanuts to feed to the drinkers on the other side of the fence.  that would really set this bar apart imo.
Great music and atmosphere.
Good bar, and you can also bring a dog!
Great beers and good tavern atmosphere.

Friendly staff, awesome outdoor space. Always make a stop here on our way home.
Because it's been right as long as its been open and still my local. Sworn loyal.

Down to earth bar with a solid rotating menu of craft beers on tap.  Large outdoor space where you can bring food (they don't sell any) and enjoy a drink.  Look out for events like brewery takeovers and their annual brewmaster chili cook-off!
Good selection of beers
Nice outdoor space and decent beer selection.
Enjoyable and interactive
Love it!!!! Great view of the park outside and good beer for the tap takeover!!!
Good relaxed bar that allows dogs and has great outdoor seating.
Very dark inside, cool deck outside!
Great place to grab a cold refreshing craft bear.
Excellent bartender!
Love the secluded dart board section.
Want to get drunk on the cheap? Cleanliness not a concern? The Gate is for you. I'm not saying this in a bad way, but just know what you're getting in to before you go.
Awesome outdoor space and plenty of taps to find something you'll like.
Nice outdoor area, beer list is pretty good, and there's always a real standout beer there, usually a vintage.
Excellent for groups, extensive beer selection.
Great outdoor spot
Nothing too special.  Decent beer list, an outdoor patio area.
great place with an outdoor seating. friendly knowledgeable bartenders!

Another awesome dog friendly bar in Park Slope. The patio is expansive and great on a nice day, and is totally packed with dogs typically. Very good, diverse beer list with a range of styles and rare brews. They even have darts and a weird goblin statue thing, so what's not to love?

I always have a great experience at the Gate, no matter when I go there. The patrons and the staff are very pleasant. Plus they let you bring in food! Great rotating beer selection among other fantastic drinks.

The Gate has an awesome outdoor space (get there early, it fills up!), is dog friendly and has a great atmosphere. Very laid back, and the bartenders are super nice. Plus, there's a great selection of beer on tap.
cheers incarnate
Grab a pint and a table outside. Then ask for the takeout menus and order up some grub! Fido has to stay on his leash while he begs for scraps!

Outdoor patio & worn wood bar are the highlights. The beer selection is alright with a few local choices thrown in, prices are pretty good for the neighborhood. The place can get packed and start to smell a bit.

I like The Gate...if I can find a seat, that is. You must come early and if you're allergic to dogs, or just don't like dogs, this isn't the place for you. Now, I love dogs AND beer, so this is a go-to place of mine on a cool night. Lots of awesome beers on tap.
Decent neighborhood bar with a large outdoor patio. Nothing terrible about this place but nothing unique or stellar, either.
Nice beer selection, maybe more than fifteen beers on tap. They have a nice patio, great for summer nights. It's pretty packed on weekends though. Dog friendly.
best outdoor patio in the neighborhood.  order in delivery from local restaurants.
